  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Insertion of a nasogastric tube (NGT) in anesthetized patients can be a disappointing
      experience. Many techniques have been explained to improve success rate along with increasing
      safety, such as forward displacement of the larynx, tube rigidity improvement methods,
      pushing it down directly through pharynx or using a guide tube. Failure of insertion under
      general anesthesia reached 50% in some publications
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
